AGI - Social-Democrat Peter Pellegrini>, supporter of the pro-Russian government of Premier Robert Fico>, won the Slovak presidential elections > with 53% of votes. The current president of Parliament > and leader of one of the three parties of the coalition of left-wing populists and ultra-nationalists > thus defeated the European Unionist Ivan Korcok >, who arrived first in the first round fifteen days ago with his message to exercise control of the executive by the head of state. Korkok stopped at 43%.
&nbsp;
During the election campaign, Pellegrini defended the need to negotiate with Russia > to end the war begun with its invasion of Ukraine, a position maintained by the government that, since it rose to power in autumn, interrupted the significant military aid that the country provided in Kiev. Urn turnout was 60%, 18 points higher than 2019.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"I am sincerely disappointed" but "I want to congratulate the winner", said Korcok, who was supported by the opposition. "I want to express my conviction that Pietro Pellegrini will be independent and will act according to his own convictions and without orders," added Korcok.&nbsp; "It is a huge satisfaction", said Peter Pellegrini, speaking in Bratislava and ensuring his commitment to " Slovakia remains on the side of peace > and not on the side of the war". &nbsp;
